body: Hi Everybody, How can I solve this err[](http://api.ning.com:80/files/*hEUPDiLn3uzc9dxWc9bAQEO0UmmC4UvefdhaCtrinBxlq7c*7Guhli8Sc37zH291HhpLbSOLHskM4zyOv*4at9B4s8LrgxI/11.png)or?

replies.body: Check if the EnergyPlus simulation ran correctly.

Hi Mostapha;

I install Energyplus again but I have this error.What can I do?

   Best Regards,

       Sajjad

I took a look at your file Sajad, and you're using an older version of HB/LB and also seem to be accidently(?) adding the HBZones twice to one of the components. I updated your HB/LB components (for future reference you can use the UpdateHoneybee component to do this) and ran the energy simulation using the openstudio component, and it works. 

See file below, let me know if it works.

[
](http://api.ning.com:80/files/offRlRpFlkh9FRzBiDiCD9ql26XE6wYg1CO7YXIK1g8aYU2ZQOQ-BYly5Gb5JwcBJ5io*J20SUTCmEoTwSsVGkud5FdPusvA/1.png)[](http://api.ning.com:80/files/offRlRpFlkhFQbY6XsfdFhoFkJybE70kTXllgn9pXhUiBVLCNlV6qcJlIvF-oGEJFeF5MVEDyLoVfeQq2llxMaS1gh5pNB65/1.png)Hi Saeran, I apologize you for answering late.Unfortunately I couldn't run again and encounter with new errors. how can I solve it?

Hi Sajad, As you probably know this, In LB & HB components,The "Required" Inputs has only one "_underline" before their names (left side). It is needed to connect all of the _required inputs of components to run. In this attachment, _zonedata (from "Read EP Result component) is not connected, then set boolean to true. [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/offRlRpFlkjFtcdqp7C2G7WXB9rr*pcOBWvkDy*kk-XAUw8tE1o1QyX2Kl23TJn5-Kuz8G54w7*on5b38Mpht9nnf1oLM5mE/screenshot_20161013_142855.jpg)Regards, -Omid

Sajad,

Yes, I was tested the file and works fine for me too.

Try to check Saeran's suggestions.



-Omid

Hey Salad, Omid, 

I don't think there's anything wrong with the script as its working perfectly fine for me (see img).



Some questions:

- What model units is your Rhino file set to? Should be in meters. 

- Where is the origin cplane in your Rhino file, make sure it is as close as possible to your model

- Can you make a simple box and see if the energy simulation works on that? That way we can rule out if there is a geometry issue causing this problem. 



Give that a shot, and get back to us. 



S

Saeran,Omid, I used a simple box (see img) and my model unit is meter.but I encounter with those errors again. What is wrong? Could you use with EP Run energy simulation component instead of OS component?

regards.
